In total, 24 studies with 2 584 patients were included in this investigation. Among them, 1 312 patients in the intervention group received TCM with liver-soothing function and 1 272 patients in the control group received conventional western medicine or other TCM. TCM with liver-soothing function outperformed the control group in terms of clinical efficacy. Furthermore, TCM with liver-soothing function significantly decreased HMG-associated adverse events, breast pain score, lump score, and other scores.
